#Tuberculosis is curable & preventable yet remains one of the world’s deadliest disease threats as the #COVID19 pandemic has undermined global progress. See a new 
@CDCMMWR
 for how CDC and many others are working to achieve a world without TB. http://bit.ly/7012a4

Despite the #COVID19 pandemic, an additional 208,000 Nigerians living with #HIV began treatment through CDC’s Antiretroviral Therapy Surge program supported by the U.S. President’s Emergency Plan for AIDS Relief, a new 
@CDCMMWR
 finds. Learn more: http://bit.ly/7012a3.
